The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms for classification and regression problems, specifically focusing on monotonic ordinal classification. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of noise filtering algorithms, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM). The experiments involve datasets that may involve image or video data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the use of predictive models, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
